<Link id="l00081" /><CodeLine lineNumber="81"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Identify a debugger for &quot;tuning&quot; the debug info.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00082" /><CodeLine lineNumber="82"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00083" /><CodeLine lineNumber="83"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// The &quot;debugger tuning&quot; concept allows us to present a more intuitive</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00084" /><CodeLine lineNumber="84"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// interface that unpacks into different sets of defaults for the various</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00085" /><CodeLine lineNumber="85"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// individual feature-flag settings, that suit the preferences of the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00086" /><CodeLine lineNumber="86"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// various debuggers.  However, it&#39;s worth remembering that debuggers are</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00087" /><CodeLine lineNumber="87"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// not the only consumers of debug info, and some variations in DWARF might</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00088" /><CodeLine lineNumber="88"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// better be treated as target/platform issues. Fundamentally,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00089" /><CodeLine lineNumber="89"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// o if the feature is useful (or not) to a particular debugger, regardless</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00090" /><CodeLine lineNumber="90"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   of the target, that&#39;s a tuning decision;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00402" /><CodeLine lineNumber="402" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/targetoptions/#a44277c39cd6496cc63dace4b1eb36bb7"><span class="doxyHighlight">    <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/floatabi/#aea077c52d84934aabf9445cef9eab2e2">FloatABI::ABIType</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/targetoptions/#a44277c39cd6496cc63dace4b1eb36bb7">FloatABIType</a> = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/floatabi/#aea077c52d84934aabf9445cef9eab2e2ae41bda228a5aa7298dc5ac9cff9414f2">FloatABI::Default</a>;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00403" /><CodeLine lineNumber="403"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00404" /><CodeLine lineNumber="404"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// AllowFPOpFusion - This flag is set by the -fp-contract=xxx option.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00405" /><CodeLine lineNumber="405"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// This controls the creation of fused FP ops that store intermediate</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00406" /><CodeLine lineNumber="406"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// results in higher precision than IEEE allows (E.g. FMAs).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00407" /><CodeLine lineNumber="407"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00408" /><CodeLine lineNumber="408"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// Fast mode - allows formation of fused FP ops whenever they&#39;re</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00409" /><CodeLine lineNumber="409"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// profitable.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00410" /><CodeLine lineNumber="410"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// Standard mode - allow fusion only for &#39;blessed&#39; FP ops. At present the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00411" /><CodeLine lineNumber="411"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// only blessed op is the fmuladd intrinsic. In the future more blessed ops</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00412" /><CodeLine lineNumber="412"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// may be added.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00413" /><CodeLine lineNumber="413"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// Strict mode - allow fusion only if/when it can be proven that the excess</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00414" /><CodeLine lineNumber="414"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// precision won&#39;t effect the result.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00415" /><CodeLine lineNumber="415"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00416" /><CodeLine lineNumber="416"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// Note: This option only controls formation of fused ops by the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00417" /><CodeLine lineNumber="417"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// optimizers.  Fused operations that are explicitly specified (e.g. FMA</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00418" /><CodeLine lineNumber="418"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// via the llvm.fma.&#42; intrinsic) will always be honored, regardless of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00419" /><CodeLine lineNumber="419"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// the value of this option.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00420" /><CodeLine lineNumber="420" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/targetoptions/#affeb69a55c900f2d333c385955676931"><span class="doxyHighlight">    <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/fpopfusion/#a9c71bae9f02af273833fde586d529fc5">FPOpFusion::FPOpFusionMode</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/targetoptions/#affeb69a55c900f2d333c385955676931">AllowFPOpFusion</a> = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/fpopfusion/#a9c71bae9f02af273833fde586d529fc5aff3d2f74200c0252e2912c6b605d94e9">FPOpFusion::Standard</a>;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00421" /><CodeLine lineNumber="421"></CodeLine>
